    Scope and Contents
STEAMBOATS AND INLAND RIVERS
Johnny Lawhead, ferry operator, and Emory Edgington, captain, each discuss their riverboat experiences. Lawhead discusses his ferry operation between Coney Island (near Cincinnati) and Brent, Kentucky. Edgington recalls experiences with steamboats, towboats, coal hauling, and weather on Ohio rivers.2 tapes, 14 pp.
Interviews by John Knoepfle, 1957
